    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>HOLD YOUR CEREAL BOXES TIGHT!</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20091001.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, October  1, 2009</b> &mdash;
    The <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">trail</a> of cereal crumbs and <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">Cookie Crisp&reg; cereal boxes</a> scattered throughout town raised everyone&#039;s suspicions. But when Inspector Nelson lifted a set of fingerprints from one of the boxes, the results were still a bit of a shock. <br><br>Sure enough, the oddly shaped prints belonged to none other than the cereal-loving Chip the Wolf! And Inspector Nelson, whose favorite cereal just happens to be Cookie Crisp, knew what this meant. <br><br>Chip the Wolf is known for his Cookie Crisp cereal obsession, and for using trickery to distract people so he can snag their Cookie Crisp cereal boxes! In other words, this isn&#039;t the first time Chip has attempted to do this. <br><br>But the last time he appeared, he promised not to return &mdash; a pledge made after seeing his face on every Cookie Crisp cereal box. Little did he know that the picture wasn&#039;t an honor salute, but rather a way to help people recognize him if they noticed someone hanging out near their cereal bowl!<br>
<br>
Given this history, Inspector Nelson now wants to equip every citizen with the tools necessary to protect their yummy boxes of delicious Cookie Crisp cereal from Chip. And you can put your Millsbucks away, because the following items can be added to your stuff, for FREE: a <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">Cookie Crisp cereal cookie trail</a>, <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">cereal boxes</a>, a <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">Cookie Crisp cereal pool</a>, a <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">hat</a> that resembles Chip&#039;s ears and furry head, and a <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">pad-locked door</a> to keep Chip out for good!<br><br>Inspector Nelson headed to the Grocery Store first, to see if owner Harold Ettin had seen any trace of Chip. He found Ettin in the breakfast aisle, staring at the wall of cereal, and studying the shelves with a magnifying glass. <br><br>&quot;Did I see Chip the Wolf? No &mdash; but I found some wolf-whiskers in aisle 2, and now I&#039;m counting the boxes to make sure none were taken!&quot;<br><br>Nelson took fingerprints and posted a &quot;Wanted&quot; sign, featuring Chip&#039;s picture, at the front of the store. He explained, &quot;I&#039;m on the case &mdash; and I won&#039;t sleep until our cereal is safe!&quot;<br><br>So get your FREE <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">pad-locked door</a>&mdash;and boxes of <a href="http://millsberry.com/cookiecrisp">Cookie Crisp cereal</a> and other great items. After all, it&#039;s too soon to tell when and if Chip will be caught... .
    </div>

